"master","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"body":"Maybe this is related to #802 \n\nI am trying to draw a health bar over a unit using a 1x1 sprite but the health bar seems to change its height when the unit is moving.\n\nHere is a test drawing a simple sprite and moving it along the y axis which reproduces this behaviour:\n\n```\n    import com.badlogic.gdx.ApplicationAdapter;\n    import com.badlogic.gdx.Gdx;\n    import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglApplication;\n    import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.Color;\n    import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.GL10;\n    import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.OrthographicCamera;\n    import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.Pixmap;\n    import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.Pixmap.Format;\n    import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.Texture;\n    import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.Sprite;\n    import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.SpriteBatch;\n    import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.TextureAtlas;\n\n    public class Test extends ApplicationAdapter {\n        SpriteBatch batch;\n        Sprite s;\n        OrthographicCamera cam = new OrthographicCamera();\n\n        @Override\n        public void create () {\n            batch = new SpriteBatch();\n            s = createDrawable(Color.YELLOW);\n            s.setSize(20, 2);\n            cam.setToOrtho(false, 100, 100);\n        }\n\n        Sprite createDrawable (Color c) {\n            Pixmap p = new Pixmap(4, 4, Format.RGBA8888);\n            p.setColor(c);\n            p.drawPixel(1, 1);\n            TextureAtlas atlas = new TextureAtlas();\n            atlas.addRegion(\"white\", new Texture(p), 1, 1, 1, 1);\n            return atlas.createSprite(\"white\");\n        }\n\n        float y;\n\n        @Override\n        public void render () {\n            Gdx.gl.glClear(GL10.GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT);\n            Gdx.gl.glClearColor(0, 0, 0, 1);\n            cam.update();\n            batch.setProjectionMatrix(cam.combined);\n\n            y += 1 * Gdx.graphics.getDeltaTime();\n            s.setPosition(10, y);\n            batch.begin();\n            s.draw(batch);\n            batch.end();\n        }\n\n        public static void main (String[] args) {\n            new LwjglApplication(new Test());\n        }\n    }\n```\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/816/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/816/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"}]